<div style="font-size:18px";>
<p style="text-align:center"; ,style="font-size:210px";>Entering the world of medical education through the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test (NEET) demands a comprehensive understanding of its eligibility criteria. Aspiring medical professionals need to go through a defined set of rules and requirements set by the National Testing Agency (NTA). NTA is an exam-conducting organization that conducts the NEET exam every year.</p> 
<h1> NEET Eligibility Criteria 2024 For Indians</h1>
<ul>1)Candidates must have completed or be appearing for the 10+2 examination or its equivalent from a recognized board or university.</ul>
<ul>2)Indian candidates, similar to others, must obtain a minimum aggregate of 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry, and Biology/Biotechnology in the qualifying examination.</ul>
<ul>3)The minimum age requirement for Indian candidates to appear for NEET 2024 is 17 years. There is no maximum NEET age limit for Indian candidates.</ul>
<ul>4)Indian citizens are eligible to apply for NEET 2024, and they need to fulfill the specified educational and age criteria for successful application.</ul>
<H1>NEET Eligibility Marks in 12th</H1>
<P style="text-align:center";>1)For NEET UG 2024, candidates must adhere to specific eligibility criteria concerning marks obtained in the 12th standard. General category candidates need a minimum aggregate of 50% marks in Physics, Chemistry, and Biology combined.<BR>

2)Meanwhile, candidates from SC/ST/OBC-NCL categories should secure a minimum of 40% marks in these subjects. It is essential for candidates to meet these criteria to qualify for the NEET UG 2024 examination.</P>
